    <h1>Business English Certificate </h1>
    <h3>About</h3>
    <p>To survive in today's highly competitive world, it has become imperative for graduates have certain edge. 
        Recognizing the importance of this, and the fact that communication skills play a major role in recruitments,
         KMIT offers its students an opportunity to take the Business English Certificate exam, an ESOL exam conducted by Cambridge University,
         more commonly known as BEC.</p>
    <p>Needless to say, BEC is an internationally recognized qualification in English for work. The benefits of getting the certification are many:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>It provides language Skills for real life business situations</li>
        <li>Improves employability and career prospects</li>
        <li>Clear, reliable evidence of language abilities.</li>
        <li>It is trusted by Employers and Universities alike, in more than 60 countries</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The certificate is available at three levels - BEC Preliminary, BEC Vantage and BEC Higher. At present, KMIT provides coaching for Preliminary and Vantage levels.</p>
    <h3>Faculty</h3>
    <h4>Dr. Aparna</h4>
    <p>A PhD with 25 years of teaching experience. Besides regular teaching, Dr. Aparna has worked as a counselor for students studying certificate course in functional English at IGNOU; for M.A. literature students at B.R. Ambedkar University and a counselor at the ELT Centre at Nizam College. She is also a trained Soft Skills expert from Osmania University and has conducted workshops at schools and colleges. Dr. Aparna is a course instructor for Business English Certificate Preliminary level.</p>
    <h4>Shweta Paropkari</h4>
    <p>An ELT (English Language Trainer) armed with a Masters’ Degree, Ms. Paropkari has been working exclusively with Engineering students for the past four years.She brings along with her a corporate experience having worked with Deloitte India Private Services prior to becoming a dedicated language trainer . She is a certified BEC and Soft Skills Trainer and has worked with several engineering institutes across India. Ms. Paropkari is the course instructor for both Preliminary and Vantage levels of BEC.</p>
